         <abstract>
            <p>Lowering the subscription price increases the probability of a successful issue and has no adverse impact on stock price performance following the issue. Financial managers should, therefore, concentrate on minimizing the primary risk-the risk that the market price will fall below the subscription price during the offering period.</p>
